{
  "texts": [
    "Solitons over Riemann surfaces: Proof of Corollary D. In this subsection we briefly return to considering Ricci solitons constructed using Ansatz 3.1 via Proposition 3.4.",
    "Our main aim is to prove Corollary D. We also prove a necessary condition for solitons satisfying Ansatz 3.1 to be homogeneous.",
    "Let Σ = (B 2, c) be a Riemann surface, with χ(B 2) < 0.",
    "Combining Theorem C with Proposition 3.4, we can associate a Ricci soliton to a polystable Higgs bundle.",
    "Notice that we must make several choices for this association, but different choices lead to isometric solitons."
  ]
}